sql:
SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM album_ratings
WHERE album_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- The logarithm to the base 2 (LOG2) is used here to reduce the impact of extreme values in rating counts, making the differences between counts more comparable; 
- Topmost genres refer to genres at the top of the hierarchical structure that do not have a parent genre; 
- The comparison to the next highest rated album is only applicable when there are multiple albums within the same genre, highlighting how an album's rating stands in relation to its peers within the same genre.
